<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<search>
  <entry>
    <title>Frequently used Java syntax</title>
    <url>/2020/04/02/Frequently-used-Java-syntax/</url>
    <content><![CDATA[<p>Summarize my frequently used Java syntax and make it convenient for lookup.<br>Suggestions are welcome.  </p>
<p><em>Original post by Qianyue Zhang in Apr 2020</em>  </p>
<p>(keep posting …)</p>
<a id="more"></a>
<h4 id="Arrays"><a href="#Arrays" class="headerlink" title="Arrays"></a>Arrays</h4><figure class="highlight fsharp"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="class"><span class="keyword">type</span> <span class="title">var</span>-<span class="title">name</span>[] </span>= <span class="keyword">new</span> <span class="class"><span class="keyword">type</span>[<span class="title">size</span>];</span></span><br><span class="line">OR</span><br><span class="line"><span class="class"><span class="keyword">type</span>[] <span class="title">var</span>-<span class="title">name</span> </span>= <span class="keyword">new</span> <span class="class"><span class="keyword">type</span>[<span class="title">size</span>];</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<h5 id="Built-in-methods"><a href="#Built-in-methods" class="headerlink" title="Built-in methods"></a>Built-in methods</h5><p><code>Arrays.fill(Object[] array, Object value)</code>,<br><code>Arrays.equals(Object[] array1, Object[] array2)</code>  </p>
<hr>
<figure class="highlight nimrod"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="type">Arrays</span>.sort(<span class="built_in">int</span>[] <span class="built_in">array</span>, new <span class="type">Comparator</span> &lt;<span class="built_in">int</span>[]&gt; (...)<span class="meta">&#123;...&#125;</span>)</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<p>e.g.</p>
<figure class="highlight angelscript"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">Arrays.sort(envelopes, new Comparator&lt;<span class="built_in">int</span>[]&gt;()&#123;</span><br><span class="line">           <span class="keyword">public</span> <span class="built_in">int</span> compare(<span class="built_in">int</span>[] nums1, <span class="built_in">int</span>[] nums2)&#123;</span><br><span class="line">               <span class="keyword">if</span> (nums1[<span class="number">0</span>] == nums2[<span class="number">0</span>])&#123;</span><br><span class="line">                   <span class="keyword">return</span> nums2[<span class="number">1</span>] - nums1[<span class="number">1</span>];</span><br><span class="line">               &#125;</span><br><span class="line">               <span class="keyword">return</span> nums1[<span class="number">0</span>] - nums2[<span class="number">0</span>];</span><br><span class="line">           &#125;</span><br><span class="line">        &#125;);</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<figure class="highlight reasonml"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="module-access"><span class="module"><span class="identifier">Arrays</span>.</span></span>sort(<span class="built_in">array</span>, <span class="module-access"><span class="module"><span class="identifier">Collections</span>.</span></span>reverse<span class="constructor">Order()</span>);</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<hr>
<figure class="highlight reasonml"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="module-access"><span class="module"><span class="identifier">Arrays</span>.</span></span>binary<span class="constructor">Search(<span class="params">int</span>[] <span class="params">array</span>, <span class="params">int</span> <span class="params">left</span>, <span class="params">int</span> <span class="params">right</span>, <span class="params">int</span> <span class="params">key</span>)</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<p>e.g.</p>
<figure class="highlight smali"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">int index = Arrays.binarySearch(dp, 0, len, envelope[1]);</span><br><span class="line">//index of the search key,<span class="built_in"> if </span>it is contained in the<span class="built_in"> array </span>within the specified range; otherwise, (-(insertion point) - 1). The insertion point is defined as the point at which the key would be inserted into the array</span><br><span class="line">//The<span class="built_in"> return </span>value will be &gt;= 0<span class="built_in"> if </span>and only<span class="built_in"> if </span>the key is found.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<hr>
<p><code>Array.asList(Object[] array)</code>:</p>
<p>e.g. convert array to list</p>
<figure class="highlight cmake"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="keyword">String</span>[] a = new <span class="keyword">String</span>[] &#123; <span class="string">"A"</span>, <span class="string">"B"</span>, <span class="string">"C"</span>, <span class="string">"D"</span> &#125;;</span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">List</span>&lt;<span class="keyword">String</span>&gt; <span class="keyword">list</span> = Arrays.asList(a);</span><br><span class="line">//<span class="keyword">list</span>: [<span class="string">"A"</span>, <span class="string">"B"</span>, <span class="string">"C"</span>, <span class="string">"D"</span>]</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<hr>
<p><code>Arrays.toString(Object[] array)</code>: return a string representation of the contents of the specified array.<br>e.g. present array in the string format</p>
<figure class="highlight smali"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">int[]<span class="built_in"> array </span>=<span class="built_in"> new </span>int[]&#123; 1, 2, 3, 4 &#125;;</span><br><span class="line">String str = Arrays.toString(array);</span><br><span class="line">//str: <span class="string">"[1, 2, 3, 4]"</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<hr>
<p><code>&lt;Object[] array&gt;.clone()</code>:  </p>
<figure class="highlight pgsql"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="type">int</span>[] <span class="keyword">array</span> = <span class="built_in">new</span> <span class="type">int</span>[<span class="number">10</span>];</span><br><span class="line"><span class="type">int</span>[] copy = <span class="keyword">array</span>.clone();</span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">OR</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">System</span>.arraycopy(<span class="type">int</span>[] <span class="keyword">array</span>, <span class="type">int</span> srcPos, <span class="type">int</span>[] <span class="keyword">copy</span>, <span class="type">int</span> desPos, <span class="type">int</span> length);</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<hr>
<p>e.g. get the sum of numbers in int[] array</p>
<figure class="highlight axapta"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="keyword">int</span> <span class="keyword">sum</span> = Arrays.stream(A).<span class="keyword">sum</span>();</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>

<h4 id="Character"><a href="#Character" class="headerlink" title="Character"></a>Character</h4><p>e.g.</p>
<figure class="highlight ebnf"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="attribute">int num</span> = <span class="string">'b'</span> - <span class="string">'a'</span>;</span><br><span class="line"><span class="attribute">char c</span> = <span class="string">'c'</span>;</span><br><span class="line"><span class="attribute">char d</span> = c++;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>

<hr>
<p>e.g. char -&gt; int</p>
<figure class="highlight dart"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="built_in">int</span> <span class="built_in">num</span> = <span class="string">'7'</span> - <span class="string">'0'</span> <span class="comment">//num: 7</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>

<h5 id="Built-in-methods-1"><a href="#Built-in-methods-1" class="headerlink" title="Built-in methods"></a>Built-in methods</h5><p><code>Character.toLowerCase(char c)</code><br><code>Character.isLetterOrDigit(char c)</code>: returns true if the character is a letter or digit; false otherwise.<br><code>Character.getNumericValue(char c)</code>: returns the int value that the specified Unicode character represents</p>
<h4 id="HashMap"><a href="#HashMap" class="headerlink" title="HashMap"></a>HashMap</h4><p>e.g.  </p>
<figure class="highlight processing"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="keyword">HashMap</span> &lt;Integer&gt; <span class="built_in">map</span> = <span class="keyword">new</span> <span class="keyword">HashMap</span>();</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<h5 id="Built-in-methods-2"><a href="#Built-in-methods-2" class="headerlink" title="Built-in methods"></a>Built-in methods</h5><p><code>map.keySet()</code>, <code>map.values()</code> ,<code>map.containsKey(Object key)</code>, <code>map.get(Object key)</code>, <code>map.remove(Object key)</code><br><code>map.clear()</code>: clear and remove all of the elements or mappings from a specified Map collection<br><code>map.put(Object key, Object value)</code>, <code>map.putIfAbsent(Object key, Object value)</code>:<br>returns the previous value associated with the specified key, or null if there was no mapping for the key.  </p>
<hr>
<p>e.g. for loop in map</p>
<figure class="highlight fortran"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">for (Map.<span class="built_in">Entry</span>&lt;<span class="keyword">Integer</span>, <span class="keyword">Integer</span>&gt; <span class="built_in">entry</span>: map.entrySet())&#123;</span><br><span class="line">            <span class="built_in">entry</span>.getValue();</span><br><span class="line">            <span class="built_in">entry</span>.getKey();</span><br><span class="line">        &#125;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>

<h4 id="Integer"><a href="#Integer" class="headerlink" title="Integer"></a>Integer</h4><p>range: -2^{31} ~ 2^{31} - 1</p>
<h5 id="Built-in-methods-3"><a href="#Built-in-methods-3" class="headerlink" title="Built-in methods"></a>Built-in methods</h5><p><code>Integer.bitCount(int num)</code>: returns the number of one-bits in the two’s complement binary representation of the specified int value. (number of digits in decimal)</p>
<h4 id="Math"><a href="#Math" class="headerlink" title="Math"></a>Math</h4><h5 id="Built-in-methods-4"><a href="#Built-in-methods-4" class="headerlink" title="Built-in methods"></a>Built-in methods</h5><p><code>Math.pow(double base, double exponent)</code>: Returns double<br><code>Math.sqrt(double num)</code>: Returns the correctly rounded positive square root of a double value.</p>
<h4 id="MAX-MIN"><a href="#MAX-MIN" class="headerlink" title="MAX/MIN"></a>MAX/MIN</h4><p><code>Integer.MAX_VALUE</code>, <code>Integer.MIN_VALUE</code></p>
<h4 id="List"><a href="#List" class="headerlink" title="List"></a>List</h4><p>e.g.  </p>
<figure class="highlight lasso"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">ArrayList &lt;<span class="built_in">Integer</span>&gt; <span class="built_in">list</span> = <span class="literal">new</span> ArrayList();</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<figure class="highlight lasso"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">LinkedList &lt;<span class="built_in">Integer</span>&gt; <span class="built_in">list</span> = <span class="literal">new</span> LinkedList();</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<p>e.g. create ArrayList of ArrayList  </p>
<figure class="highlight lasso"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="built_in">List</span>&lt;<span class="built_in">List</span>&lt;<span class="built_in">Integer</span>&gt;&gt; <span class="built_in">list</span> = <span class="literal">new</span> ArrayList&lt;&gt;();</span><br><span class="line"><span class="built_in">list</span>.add(<span class="literal">new</span> ArrayList&lt;<span class="built_in">Integer</span>&gt;(sub_arraylist));</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<hr>
<h5 id="Differences-between-ArrayList-and-LinkedList"><a href="#Differences-between-ArrayList-and-LinkedList" class="headerlink" title="Differences between ArrayList and LinkedList:"></a><a href="https://www.javatpoint.com/difference-between-arraylist-and-linkedlist" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Differences between ArrayList and LinkedList</a>:</h5><table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>ArrayList</th>
<th>LinkedList</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody><tr>
<td>ArrayList internally uses a <strong>dynamic array</strong> to store the elements.</td>
<td>LinkedList internally uses a <strong>doubly linked list</strong> to store the elements.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Manipulation with ArrayList is <strong>slow</strong> because it internally uses an array. If any element is removed from the array, all the bits are shifted in memory.</td>
<td>Manipulation with LinkedList is <strong>faster</strong> than ArrayList because it uses a doubly linked list, so no bit shifting is required in memory.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>An ArrayList class can <strong>act as a list</strong> only because it implements List only.</td>
<td>LinkedList class can <strong>act as a list and queue</strong> both because it implements List and Deque interfaces.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>ArrayList is <strong>better for storing and accessing</strong> data.</td>
<td>LinkedList is <strong>better for manipulating</strong> data.</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
<hr>
<h5 id="Built-in-methods-5"><a href="#Built-in-methods-5" class="headerlink" title="Built-in methods"></a>Built-in methods</h5><p><code>list.add(Object e)</code>, <code>list.remove(Object e)</code>, <code>list.get(int index)</code>, <code>list.add(int index, Object e)</code>, <code>list.set(int index, Object e)</code>, <code>list.remove(int index)</code>, <code>list.size()</code>, <code>list.contains(Object e)</code>, <code>list.isEmpty()</code><br><code>list.clear()</code>: remove all of the elements from the list<br>For LinkedList:<br><code>linkedlist.peek()</code>: returns the head of this list, or null if this list is empty<br><code>linkedlist.pollLast()</code>: Retrieves and removes the last element of this list, or returns null if this list is empty.<br><code>linkedlist.getLast()</code>: Returns the last element in this list.</p>
<hr>
<p><code>list.toArray(T[] a)</code>:  </p>
<figure class="highlight smali"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">String[]<span class="built_in"> array </span>= list.toArray(new String[list.size()]);</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<figure class="highlight markdown"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">List<span class="xml"><span class="tag">&lt;<span class="name">int[]</span>&gt;</span></span> list = new ArrayList<span class="xml"><span class="tag">&lt;&gt;</span></span>();</span><br><span class="line">int[<span class="string"></span>][<span class="symbol"></span>] array = list.toArray(new int[<span class="string">list.size()</span>][<span class="symbol">2</span>]);</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<figure class="highlight smali"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">LinkedList&lt;Integer&gt; list =<span class="built_in"> new </span>LinkedList&lt;&gt;();</span><br><span class="line">int[]<span class="built_in"> array </span>= list.stream().mapToInt(i -&gt; i).toArray();</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<h4 id="Long"><a href="#Long" class="headerlink" title="Long"></a>Long</h4><h5 id="Built-in-methods-6"><a href="#Built-in-methods-6" class="headerlink" title="Built-in methods"></a>Built-in methods</h5><p>e.g. convert string to long type:</p>
<figure class="highlight reasonml"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">long <span class="keyword">val</span> = <span class="module-access"><span class="module"><span class="identifier">Long</span>.</span></span>parse<span class="constructor">Long(<span class="string">"1234"</span>)</span>;</span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment">//val: 1234</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<p>e.g. cast long to int:</p>
<figure class="highlight reasonml"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="built_in">int</span> num = <span class="module-access"><span class="module"><span class="identifier">Math</span>.</span></span><span class="keyword">to</span><span class="constructor">IntExact(<span class="params">val</span>)</span>;</span><br><span class="line">OR</span><br><span class="line"><span class="built_in">int</span> num = (<span class="built_in">int</span>)<span class="keyword">val</span>;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>

<h4 id="Queue"><a href="#Queue" class="headerlink" title="Queue"></a>Queue</h4><p>e.g.  </p>
<figure class="highlight routeros"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">Queue &lt;Integer&gt;<span class="built_in"> queue </span>= new LinkedList&lt;Integer&gt;();</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<h5 id="Built-in-methods-7"><a href="#Built-in-methods-7" class="headerlink" title="Built-in methods"></a>Built-in methods</h5><p><code>queue.add(Object e)</code>, <code>queue.isEmpty()</code>, <code>queue.size()</code><br> <code>queue.poll()</code>: Retrieves and removes the head of this queue, or returns null if this queue is empty.<br> <code>queue.remove()</code>: Retrieves and removes the head of this queue. This method differs from poll only in that it throws an exception if this queue is empty.<br> <code>queue.peek()</code>: Retrieves, but does not remove, the head of this queue, or returns null if this queue is empty.</p>
<h4 id="Priority-Queue"><a href="#Priority-Queue" class="headerlink" title="Priority Queue"></a>Priority Queue</h4><p>e.g.  </p>
<figure class="highlight lasso"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">PriorityQueue &lt;<span class="built_in">Integer</span>&gt; heap = <span class="literal">new</span> PriorityQueue &lt;<span class="built_in">Integer</span>&gt;();</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<figure class="highlight coffeescript"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">ListNode[] lists = <span class="keyword">new</span> ListNode[]&#123;&lt;ListNode&gt;, &lt;ListNode&gt;, ...&#125;</span><br><span class="line">PriorityQueue &lt;ListNode&gt; heap = <span class="keyword">new</span> PriorityQueue&lt;ListNode&gt;(lists.length, <span class="function"><span class="params">(a, b)</span> -&gt;</span> a.val - b.val);</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<figure class="highlight reasonml"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">PriorityQueue &lt;Integer&gt; heap = <span class="keyword">new</span> PriorityQueue&lt;&gt;(<span class="module-access"><span class="module"><span class="identifier">Collections</span>.</span></span>reverse<span class="constructor">Order()</span>);</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<h5 id="Built-in-methods-8"><a href="#Built-in-methods-8" class="headerlink" title="Built-in methods"></a>Built-in methods</h5><p><code>heap.offer(Object e)</code>, <code>heap.isEmpty()</code><br><code>heap.poll()</code>: Retrieves and removes the head of this queue, or returns null if this queue is empty.</p>
<h4 id="Set"><a href="#Set" class="headerlink" title="Set"></a>Set</h4><p>e.g.  </p>
<figure class="highlight gams"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">HashSet &lt;<span class="keyword">Integer</span>&gt; <span class="keyword">set</span> = new <span class="comment">HashSet()</span>;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<figure class="highlight gams"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">TreeSet &lt;<span class="keyword">Integer</span>&gt; <span class="keyword">set</span> = new <span class="comment">TreeSet()</span>;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<h5 id="Built-in-methods-9"><a href="#Built-in-methods-9" class="headerlink" title="Built-in methods"></a>Built-in methods</h5><p><code>set.add(Object e)</code>, <code>set.contains(Object e)</code>, <code>set.remove(Object e)</code>, <code>set.size()</code><br>For TreeSet - O(logn):<br><code>treeset.floor(Object e)</code>: returns the greatest element less than or equal to e, or null if there is no such element.<br><code>treeset.ceiling(Object e)</code>: returns the least element greater than or equal to e, or null if there is no such element.<br><code>treeset.last()</code>: returns the highest member of the set. If the elements are of string type then they are checked in alphabetical order irrespective of length and if the elements are of integer types then the largest integer is returned. The string of alphabet types is given higher priority.</p>
<h4 id="Stack"><a href="#Stack" class="headerlink" title="Stack"></a>Stack</h4><p>e.g.</p>
<figure class="highlight lasso"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="built_in">Stack</span> &lt;<span class="built_in">Integer</span>&gt; <span class="built_in">stack</span> = <span class="literal">new</span> <span class="built_in">Stack</span>();</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<h5 id="Built-in-methods-10"><a href="#Built-in-methods-10" class="headerlink" title="Built-in methods"></a>Built-in methods</h5><p><code>stack.push(Object e)</code>, <code>stack.pop()</code>, <code>stack.empty()</code>/<code>stack.isEmpty()</code>, <code>stack.peek()</code></p>
<h4 id="String"><a href="#String" class="headerlink" title="String"></a>String</h4><h5 id="Built-in-methods-11"><a href="#Built-in-methods-11" class="headerlink" title="Built-in methods"></a>Built-in methods</h5><p><code>&lt;String&gt;.substring(int start, int end)</code>, <code>&lt;String&gt;.startsWith(String prefix)</code>, <code>&lt;String&gt;.isEmpty()</code>, <code>&lt;String A&gt;.equals(&lt;String B&gt;)</code>, <code>&lt;String&gt;.charAt(int index)</code>, <code>&lt;String&gt;.toLowerCase()</code></p>
<hr>
<p><code>&lt;String&gt;.toCharArray()</code>:  </p>
<p>e.g.  </p>
<figure class="highlight pgsql"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">String str = "String";</span><br><span class="line"><span class="type">char</span>[] <span class="keyword">array</span>= str.toCharArray();</span><br><span class="line">//<span class="keyword">array</span>: &#123;<span class="string">'S'</span>, <span class="string">'t'</span>, <span class="string">'r'</span>, <span class="string">'i'</span>, <span class="string">'n'</span>, <span class="string">'g'</span>&#125;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<hr>
<p><code>new String(char[] array)</code>, <code>new String(char[] array, int start, int length)</code>, <code>String.valueOf(char[] array)</code>  </p>
<p>e.g. convert char[] array back to String</p>
<figure class="highlight reasonml"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">str = <span class="keyword">new</span> <span class="constructor">String(<span class="params">array</span>)</span>;</span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment">//str: "String"</span></span><br><span class="line">str = <span class="keyword">new</span> <span class="constructor">String(<span class="params">array</span>, 0, 3)</span>;</span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment">//str: "Str"</span></span><br><span class="line">OR</span><br><span class="line">str = <span class="module-access"><span class="module"><span class="identifier">String</span>.</span></span>value<span class="constructor">Of(<span class="params">array</span>)</span>;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<hr>
<p><code>&lt;String A&gt;.compareTo(&lt;String B&gt;)</code>:<br>145. Binary Tree Postorder Traversal<br>returns 0 if A equal to B;<br>returns &lt; 0 if A is lexicographically less than B;<br>returns &gt; 0 if A is lexicographically greater than B;  </p>
<hr>
<p><code>&lt;String&gt;.split()</code>:</p>
<figure class="highlight smalltalk"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="type">String</span> text = <span class="comment">"we will we will rock you"</span>;</span><br><span class="line"><span class="type">String</span>[] words = text.split(<span class="comment">" "</span>);</span><br><span class="line">//words: &#123;<span class="comment">"we"</span>, <span class="comment">"will"</span>, <span class="comment">"we"</span>, <span class="comment">"will"</span>, <span class="comment">"rock"</span>, <span class="comment">"you"</span>&#125;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<h4 id="StringBuilder"><a href="#StringBuilder" class="headerlink" title="StringBuilder"></a>StringBuilder</h4><p>e.g.</p>
<pre><code>StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();</code></pre><h5 id="Built-in-methods-12"><a href="#Built-in-methods-12" class="headerlink" title="Built-in methods"></a>Built-in methods</h5><p><code>sb.append(char c)</code>, <code>sb.append(int n)</code>, <code>sb.toString()</code>, <code>sb.insert(int index, String/int/char c)</code>, <code>sb.reverse()</code><br><code>sb.setLength(int newlength)</code>: setting newlength to 0 will empty SB</p>
