    <content><![CDATA[<p><img data-src="/images/sc_index.jpg" alt="">  </p>
<a id="more"></a>  
<p style="text-align: center; border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;"> Index </p>  

<p><img data-src="/images/sc_profile.jpg" alt="">  </p>
<p style="text-align: center; border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;"> Profile </p>  

<p><img data-src="/images/sc_sell.jpg" alt="">  </p>
<p style="text-align: center; border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;"> Sell / Edit </p>  

<p><img data-src="/images/sc_detail.jpg" alt="">  </p>
<p style="text-align: center; border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;"> Detail </p>  

<p><img data-src="/images/sc_comment.jpg" alt="">  </p>
<p style="text-align: center; border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;"> Comment / Reply </p>  

<p><img data-src="/images/sc_notification.png" alt="">  </p>
<p style="text-align: center; border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;"> Notification </p>  

<h4 id="🌟-Built-with"><a href="#🌟-Built-with" class="headerlink" title="🌟 Built with"></a>🌟 Built with</h4><p>• JavaScript<br>• HTML &amp; CSS<br>• Node.js<br>• Express<br>• MongoDB<br>• Heroku  </p>
<h4 id="🌟-Components"><a href="#🌟-Components" class="headerlink" title="🌟 Components"></a>🌟 Components</h4><p>• Database —&gt; <a href="https://www.mongodb.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">MongoDB</a><br>• Deployment —&gt; <a href="https://www.heroku.com/platform" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Heroku</a>  </p>
<h4 id="🌟-Features"><a href="#🌟-Features" class="headerlink" title="🌟 Features"></a>🌟 Features</h4><p>Authentication:<br>• login / signup / logout  </p>
<p>Index Page:<br>• Browse posts of second-hand books on sale published by other users<br>• Search sale information of specific second-hand books by the search bar<br>• Brief profile information on side  </p>
<p>Profile Page:<br>• Edit username and contact information<br>• Check the number of own books on sale / the number of own books sold<br>• Browse brief information of own posts<br>• Other users can check the profile but only in guest view (editing functions are hidden)  </p>
<p>Sell Book Page (also Edit Book information Page):<br>• Create a new post by filling the information form and upload the picture of the book<br>• Edit one existing post later<br>• Mark the book ‘on sale’ or ‘sold’   </p>
<p>Book Detail Page:<br>• Show the owner of the book and other books information<br>• Other users can claim the book by clicking “I want this” to send a notification to the owner<br>• Comment and reply under the post  </p>
<p>Notification Page:<br>Receive notifications if<br>• some users want to buy certain own books<br>• some users commented under certain own posts<br>• some users replied own comments under certain posts  </p>
<h4 id="📌-Note"><a href="#📌-Note" class="headerlink" title="📌 Note"></a>📌 Note</h4><p>• Information of books in the example were randomly selected from <a href="https://search.library.utoronto.ca/index" target="_blank" rel="noopener">U of T library</a><br>• Background image (and alt image in the ‘upload the picture of the book’ area) was from Google Image<br>• Modified from my course project. Thanks to teammates <a href="https://github.com/AlexChum" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Alex</a>, <a href="https://github.com/ritadi" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Rita</a>, <a href="https://github.com/glebka100500" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hlib</a> and our instructor <a href="https://github.com/mark-kazakevich" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Mark</a>    </p>
]]></content>
